 <div class="card" style="grid-column:1/-1"><h3>Monte Carlo Financial Resilience Processor</h3><p class="muted">Run 500 randomized household scenarios. This is a teaching simulation, not a forecast or advice.</p><div class="three"><div><label>Starting emergency savings</label><input id="mcSavings" type="number" value="2500"><label>Monthly net income</label><input id="mcIncome" type="number" value="3200"><label>Income volatility %</label><input id="mcIncomeVol" type="number" value="12"></div><div><label>Monthly essential costs</label><input id="mcCosts" type="number" value="2600"><label>Cost volatility %</label><input id="mcCostVol" type="number" value="10"><label>Shock probability per month %</label><input id="mcShockProb" type="number" value="12"></div><div><label>Typical shock cost</label><input id="mcShockCost" type="number" value="900"><label>Months to simulate</label><input id="mcMonths" type="number" value="12"><label>Monthly saving/investing goal</label><input id="mcGoal" type="number" value="150"></div></div><button class="btn primary" onclick="AFH.runMonteCarlo()">Run Financial Simulation</button><pre id="mcOut" style="white-space:pre-wrap;background:rgba(0,0,0,.24);padding:12px;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(217,184,120,.24);min-height:120px"></pre></div>
